description.value: Four joining sherds (with 1924,1201.963 and 967) of rim and wall of large North Ionian black-figured pottery bowl. Interior streakily glazed save for reserved band below rim; at mid-wall, between added red bands lined with white, frieze in white of alternating triple verticals and sets of three concentric circles lined with dots; below, remains of incised decoration (tongues?).
